citations:
    citation-affc-brienne-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Brienne I"
            text_from_source: "I am looking for a maid of three-and-ten, she told the grey-haired goodwife beside the village well. A highborn maid and very beautiful, with blue eyes and auburn hair. She may have been traveling with a portly knight of forty years, or perhaps with a fool. Have you seen her?"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Brienne of Tarth. Brienne is searching for Sansa Stark, riding the road toward Duskendale. She meets hedge knights Ser Creighton Longbough and Ser Illifer the Penniless. Ser Illifer identifies the shield Jaime gave Brienne as belonging to the cursed House Lothston (black bat, silver and gold bendwise). He accuses her of being 'the Maid of Tarth who opened Renly's royal throat.' Brienne swears by the Seven she did not harm Renly and explains she loved him. Established that Brienne carries Oathkeeper (the Valyrian steel sword Jaime gave her) and a letter from Jaime. She reasons about where Sansa might have gone. Mentions Cleos Frey died and Jaime lost his hand during their journey from Riverrun. Hedge knights Ser Creighton and Ser Illifer named."
